label.value: Lugano Classification Advanced Stage Childhood Hodgkin Lymphoma AJCC v8

label.value: Lugano Classification Stage III Childhood Hodgkin Lymphoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage III: Involvement of lymph node regions on both sides of the diaphragm; nodes above the diaphragm with spleen involvement. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Lugano Classification Stage IV Childhood Hodgkin Lymphoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IV: Diffuse or disseminated involvement of one or more extralymphatic organs, with or without associated lymph node involvement; or noncontiguous extralymphatic organ involvement in conjunction with nodal stage II disease; or any extralymphatic organ involvement in nodal stage III disease. Stage IV includes any involvement of the bone marrow, liver, or lungs (other than by direct extension in stage IIE disease). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: EXO III Motif

label.value: Lugano Classification Stage IIE Adult Hodgkin Lymphoma AJCC v8

Stage IV includes any involvement of the CSF, bone marrow, liver, or lungs (other than by direct extension in stage IIE disease). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IE

value.value: A stage term referring to Hodgkin or non-Hodgkin lymphoma involving a single extralymphatic site in the absence of nodal involvement. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Teicoplanin

value.value: A glycopeptide antibiotic complex isolated from the bacterium Actinoplanes teichomyceticus. Teicoplanin inhibits peptidoglycan polymerization, resulting in inhibition of bacterial cell wall synthesis and cell death. (NCI04)
A chromosome band present on 10q

label.value: Stage IIE

value.value: A stage term referring to Hodgkin or non-Hodgkin lymphoma with contiguous extralymphatic extension from a nodal site with or without involvement of other lymph node regions on the same side of the diaphragm. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Cytopathic Effect

value.value: Structural changes in host cells that are caused by viral invasion.

label.value: Childhood Lymphoma by AJCC v8 Stage

value.value: Staging systems for Hodgkin and non-Hodgkin lymphomas of childhood. Different systems are used for Hodgkin lymphoma and non-Hodgkin lymphoma of childhood. Staging of childhood Hodgkin lymphoma is the same as for the adult counterpart and is based on the Lugano classification criteria. The Ann Arbor staging system has been found to be inappropriate for staging of the non-Hodgkin lymphomas of childhood. The St. Jude staging system has been widely accepted and remains the recommended staging system for non-Hodgkin lymphomas of childhood. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: PSA Level Greater than or Equal to 0.05

value.value: A blood concentration of prostate specific antigen greater than or equal to 0.05 ng/mL.

label.value: PSA Level Less than 0.7

value.value: A blood concentration of prostate specific antigen less than 0.7 ng/mL.

label.value: Lymphoma by AJCC v8 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of Hodgkin lymphoma and non-Hodgkin lymphoma according to the AJCC v8 classification guidelines.

label.value: Chronic Lymphocytic Leukemia- Modified Rai Staging System

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of chronic lymphocytic leukemia according to modified Rai staging system. This system is mainly used in North America.

label.value: Rai Stage

value.value: A stage term that refers to the modified Rai staging system which is used for the staging of chronic lymphocytic leukemia.

label.value: Chronic Lymphocytic Leukemia- Binet Staging System

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of chronic lymphocytic leukemia according to Binet staging system. This system is in wide use outside the United States.

label.value: Stage A Chronic Lymphocytic Leukemia

value.value: Findings: Lymphocytosis only; Survival (months): more than 120. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
A chromosome band present on 8p

label.value: Stage B Chronic Lymphocytic Leukemia

value.value: Findings: Lymphocytosis and adenopathy; Survival (months): 95. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Stage C Chronic Lymphocytic Leukemia

value.value: Findings: Lymphocytosis, adenopathy, and enlarged spleen and/or liver; Survival (months): 72. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Binet Stage

value.value: A stage term that refers to the Binet staging system which is used for the staging of chronic lymphocytic leukemia.

label.value: 65 kDa Phosphoprotein

value.value: 65 kDa phosphoprotein (561 aa, ~63 kDa) is encoded by the cytomegalovirus UL83 gene. This protein plays a role in both the inhibition of the host antiviral immune response and the transactivation of viral major immediate-early genes.

label.value: Satisfaction with How Natural Your Reconstructed Nipples Look

value.value: A question about how satisfied or dissatisfied an individual is or was with how natural their reconstructed nipples look.

label.value: Anti-CD20 Monoclonal Antibody

value.value: Any monoclonal antibody that targets CD20.

label.value: St. Jude Stage

value.value: A stage defined according to St. Jude Children's Research Hospital staging system for childhood non-Hodgkin lymphoma.

label.value: St. Jude Childhood Non-Hodgkin Lymphoma by AJCC v8 Stage

value.value: A staging system for childhood non-Hodgkin Lymphomas based on the St. Jude Children's Research Hospital staging system. The Ann Arbor staging system has been found to be inappropriate for staging of the non-Hodgkin lymphomas of childhood. The St. Jude staging system has been widely accepted for more than three decades and remains the recommended staging system for childhood non-Hodgkin lymphomas. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: St. Jude Stage I Childhood Non-Hodgkin Lymphoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage I: A single tumor (extranodal) or single anatomic area (nodal), with the exclusion of the mediastinum or abdomen. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: St. Jude Stage II Childhood Non-Hodgkin Lymphoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage II: A single tumor (extranodal) with regional node involvement. Two or more nodal areas on the same side of the diaphragm. Two single (extranodal) tumors with or without regional node involvement on the same side of the diaphragm. A primary gastrointestinal tract tumor, usually in the ileocecal area, with or without involvement of associated mesenteric nodes only. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
A chromosome band present on 10p

label.value: St. Jude Stage III Childhood Non-Hodgkin Lymphoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage III: Two single tumors (extranodal) on opposite sides of the diaphragm. Two or more nodal areas above and below the diaphragm. All the primary intrathoracic tumors (mediastinal, pleural, and thymic). All extensive primary intra-abdominal disease. All paraspinal or epidural tumors, regardless of other tumor site(s). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: St. Jude Stage IV Childhood Non-Hodgkin Lymphoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IV: Any tumor, with initial CNS and/or bone marrow involvement. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Lymphocyte-Depleted Classic Hodgkin Lymphoma by Ann Arbor Stage

value.value: An anatomic stage for lymphocyte-depleted classic Hodgkin lymphoma based on the Ann Arbor classification criteria.

label.value: Nodular Sclerosis Classic Hodgkin Lymphoma by Ann Arbor Stage

value.value: An anatomic stage for nodular sclerosis classic Hodgkin lymphoma based on the Ann Arbor classification criteria.

label.value: Mixed Cellularity Classic Hodgkin Lymphoma by Ann Arbor Stage

value.value: An anatomic stage for mixed cellularity classic Hodgkin lymphoma based on the Ann Arbor classification criteria.

label.value: Nodular Lymphocyte Predominant B-Cell Lymphoma by Ann Arbor Stage

value.value: An anatomic stage for nodular lymphocyte predominant B-cell lymphoma based on the Ann Arbor classification criteria.

value.value: An anatomic stage for adult Hodgkin lymphoma based on the Ann Arbor classification criteria.

value.value: An anatomic stage for childhood Hodgkin lymphoma based on the Ann Arbor classification criteria.
